I was in the area for a week and was given the task of finding a steak place for my friend's wife on her birthday. I walked to every steak place to the edges of the harbor and back inland. Steaks are very expensive in a harbor town with no cattle country. Premium Angus cuts even more so. This was the absolute cheapest price that I found anywhere. Most steak houses were $75-$100+ per plate. We had a group of 9 people. Shoot me! Birthday gal insisted on a steak venue. Their prices are the lowest and very reasonable for that area. Here I am on a Saturday at 6:30 pm being told by my friends to try for a reservation for 8:00. Good luck! (I need new friends). At first it was no and then I did speak with Barbara who was extremely kind and helpful. She rearranged some things and offered 8:30. We took it and showed up early. We we seated early, introduced to Barb's best friend (her name escapes me now-my apologies) who came in special to work and wait on us. She was so upbeat and fun! The place is very old time rustic original looking. The birthday gal decided that she wanted a pasta dinner of some type instead. (You can't smack someone on their birthday). We really enjoyed everything immensely. The home baked bread was so good that my wife wanted to go back the next day just because of it. They had a jazz band and then karaoke.
